📄 Usage Guide
🔐 Register either as a Worker or a Manager (with a secret key)

📥 Workers can submit and vote on suggestions

✅ Managers receive inspection alerts and manage statuses

👁️ Only logged-in users can access the system

📊 Admin dashboard available via Django admin panel

⚙️ Environment Variables
Variable	Description
SECRET_KEY	Django secret key for cryptographic usage
DEBUG	Set to True in development
MANAGER_SECRET_KEY	Secret value for registering as manager

Note: These are stored in a .env file and not committed to GitHub.

🗃️ Database
This project uses SQLite in development.

The database (db.sqlite3) is not included in the repository.

Upon cloning the project, you must run:


python manage.py migrate
to create an empty database from the migration files.

🚫 GitHub Exclusions
The following files and folders are excluded using .gitignore:

venv/ – Python virtual environment

__pycache__/, *.pyc – compiled Python files

db.sqlite3 – SQLite database file

.env – environment variables

.idea/, .vscode/ – IDE settings

*.log, .DS_Store, Thumbs.db – system clutter

Optional: migrations/ (except __init__.py) if you prefer fresh setups

